snippet.textDisplay: To understand the latest Bad Bunny video “Yo Perreo Sola” please read... Meet Alexa Negro Luciano, a homeless transgender woman who was shot and killed in Puerto Rico after she had used the women’s bathroom at a McDonalds. Some people that were there notified the police saying that there was a “man in a woman’s costume” in the lady’s restroom and that it represented a risk to the bathroom users at the fast food restaurant. She was then found dead, with multiple gunshot wounds, in a grassland near a main road. Her death would be investigated as a hate crime. Later, the local newspaper wrote they killed “a un hombre con falda” (a man in a skirt). Hence, the Bad Bunny shirt message at The Tonight Show starring Jimmy Fallon saying… Mataron a Alexa, no a un hombre con falda which translates to “they killed Alexa not a man in a skirt.” What Bad Bunny is doing is bringing awareness to the cruel murder of a transgender woman in his new video “Yo Perreo Sola.” She had hopes and dreams and she didn’t deserve to die that way, so please before we are quick to judge Bad Bunny for his flamboyant video, read this and understand what he is trying to do, bring awareness to LGBTQ+ community and addressee Alexa’s horrid death.
